This paper deals with the problem of offline learning in automated decision systems, which is a common topic in machine learning and artificial intelligence. The paper specifically focuses on the contextual bandits model, which is a subfield of reinforcement learning. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also discusses regularization techniques and variance estimation, which are relevant to the subfields of cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science), cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), and cs.IT (Information Theory).
